{"key":"processedPost-6773511","value":{"id":6773511,"first":6773445,"last":6773511,"when":1176273416,"utime":"04/11/07 09:36 AM","content":"Hay is a terrible substrate.&nbsp; Straw is better.&nbsp; Manure is better yet.&nbsp; I've inoculated stuff all over the place.&nbsp; Just take some jars of mycelium and a bag of cow manure from the local nursery.&nbsp; Mix them together and cover with 1/2\" of soil.&nbsp; Water with whatever is handy.&nbsp; Stream water, tap water, etc.&nbsp; It need not be sterile because nothing is sterile outdoors.<br /><br />The grow below is from a few years ago at the local botanical gardens.&nbsp; When I found out they use manure from the mounted police department stables, I couldn't resist visiting after hours with a few jars. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/lol.gif\" alt=\":lol:\" title=\":lol:\"/><br />RR<br /><br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/05-38/717919428-IMGA1281aaa.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/05-38/717919428-thumb_IMGA1281aaa.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: Moe's Outdoor Tek...","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}